        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 12 at 12:53PM EDT until July 12 at 1:15PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 1253 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Novi, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
West Bloomfield around 100 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Orchard
Lake, Commerce, Wolverine Lake, New Hudson, Farmington, Walled Lake,
Wixom, Farmington Hills, and Waterford.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
